Add global hotkey support (#724)Design:rnrnUse the plain string for both config and hotkey parsingrnand make use of KeyConverter, ModifierKeysConverterrnto make it more rubust.rnrnFind corresponding label (to display operation result) and callback (to do the real work) based on textbox name. In this case, they should be named as `<Feature-Name><Control-Name>`.rnrnShowLogsTextBox,rnShowLogsLabel,rnShowLogsCallback.rnrnIf this requirement doesn't meet, throw an exception at runtime.rnrnLogic:rnrnHow to input keys:rn1. put focus in the corresponding textboxrn2. press the key combination you want to usern3. when you think it is ready, release all keysrn4. the textbox shows your inputrnrnHow to change keys:rn1. put focus in the corresponding textboxrn2. press BackSpace to clear contentrn3. re-input new onernrnHow to deactivate:rn1. clear content in the textboxrn2. press OK buttonrnrnMeaning of label color:rn- Green: this combination is not occupied by other programs and register successfullyrn- Yellow: this combination is occupied by other programs and you have to change to another onern- Transparent without color: initial statusrnrnSigned-off-by: Syrone Wong <wong.syrone@gmail.com>

Fix a bug that a TCPHandler may be shutdown immediately after creation.Becuase we put handler.Start() call after timeout check andnlastActivity is initialized in Start(), this will lead to anincorrect timeout.nnAlso because we will call handler.Start() right after thenconstructor and timeout check, so it makes no differencenwhere we put the initializtion of lastActivity.
